apps/mobile/src/app/(app)/quiz/play.tsx lines 262-266: `handleSaveAndQuit` closes the quit modal and calls `submitRound()`. When the last question was already answered and `roundSubmittedRef.current === true` (auto-save in flight), `submitRound()` returns immediately at line 206 without navigating. The modal closes but the results screen never loads â€” the user is stuck on the play screen with no feedback.

Minimal fix: detect in-flight state in `handleSaveAndQuit` and let the already-running auto-save's `onSuccess` drive navigation:
```ts
const handleSaveAndQuit = () => {
  if (resultsRef.current.length === 0) return;
  setQuitConfirmVisible(false);
  if (roundSubmittedRef.current) {
    pendingResultsNavigateRef.current = true;
    return; // auto-save in flight; onSuccess will navigate
  }
  submitRound();
};
```
